<h2>What is S.S. Toolkit?</h2>
<p>SSToolkit is a collection of <a href="/documentation">well-documented</a> iOS classes for making life easier by solving common problems all iOS developers face. Some really handy classes are <a href="/documentation/Classes/SSCollectionView">SSCollectionView</a>, <a href="/documentation/Classes/SSGradientView">SSGradientView</a>, <a href="/documentation/Classes/SSSwitch">SSSwitch</a>, and <a href="/documentation">any many more</a>.</p>

<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<p>SSToolkit aims to be as easy to use as possible. There are some limitations on distributing iOS libraries, so this is the simplest way to get started with SSToolkit. It's painless after this, promise.</p>

