<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>To use SSToolkit, simply add the following line to your source file. I recommend adding this to your prefix to make things easy.</p>

<pre><code><span class="brown">#import</span> <span class="red">&lt;SSToolkit/SSToolkit.h&gt;</span></code></pre>

<p>You can also import individual files instead of the whole framework (for faster compile times) by doing something like:</p>

<pre><code><span class="brown">#import</span> <span class="red">&lt;SSToolkit/SSCollectionView.h&gt;</span></code></pre>

<p>If you are going to use SSToolkit's categories, you will need to import then separately (since some people might not want to use them). You import them like this:</p>

<pre><code><span class="brown">#import</span> <span class="red">&lt;SSToolkit/SSCategories.h&gt;</span></code></pre>

